    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Backend-Verse"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"64d11a3b-4b7f-58f7-8abd-648658e3b39b","excerpt":"A function represents a block of statements which performs a specific task. A function declaration tells us function name, return type and input parameters…","html":"<p>A function represents a block of statements which performs a specific task.</p>\n<p>A function declaration tells us function name, return type and input parameters.</p>\n<p>Function definition represents the code contained in the function.</p>\n<p>The syntax for declaring the function is</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\"><span class=\"token keyword\">func</span> <span class=\"token function\">function_name</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>parameter_1 <span class=\"token keyword\">type</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> parameter_n <span class=\"token keyword\">type</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> return_type <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">//statements</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The parameters and return types are optional. Also, you can return multiple values from a function.</p>\n<p>Let’s run the following example. Here function named calc will accept 2 numbers and performs the addition and subtraction and returns both values.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"go\"><pre class=\"language-go\"><code class=\"language-go\"><span class=\"token keyword\">package</span> main\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"fmt\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Calc is the function name which accepts two integers num1 and num2</span>\n<span class=\"token comment\">// (int, int) says that the function returns two values, both of integer type.</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">func</span> <span class=\"token function\">calc</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>num1 <span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> num2 <span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token builtin\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\tsum <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> num1 <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> num2\n\tdiff <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> num1 <span class=\"token operator\">-</span> num2\n\t<span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> sum<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> diff\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">func</span> <span class=\"token function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n\tx<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> y <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token number\">15</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">10</span>\n\t<span class=\"token comment\">// Calls the function calc with x and y an d gets sum, diff as output</span>\n\tsum<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> diff <span class=\"token operator\">:=</span> <span class=\"token function\">calc</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>x<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> y<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\tfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Sum\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> sum<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\tfmt<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">Println</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Diff\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> diff<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The output will be</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">Sum 25\nDiff 5</code></pre></div>","frontmatter":{"title":"Functions","date":"November 02, 2021","description":"Functions in Go?"}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/golang/slices/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Slices"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/golang/packages/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Packages"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"64d11a3b-4b7f-58f7-8abd-648658e3b39b","previousPostId":"1ebd6a32-35c9-58d8-aaca-6013b05615da","nextPostId":"b3c4e43f-243f-5c21-852b-aa55f8293e16"}},
